title: Moderate Mag. 4.6 Earthquake - North Pacific Ocean, 126 km Southeast of Petropavlovsk-Kamchatskiy, Kamchatka, Russia, on Thursday, Nov 20, 2025, at 08:41 pm (GMT +11)
text:
A strong magnitude 4.6 earthquake occurred in the North Pacific Ocean 292 km (181 mi) from Russia in the evening of Thursday, Nov 20, 2025 at 8.41 pm local time (GMT +11). The quake had a shallow depth of 64 km (40 mi) and was not felt (or at least not reported so).
